    "body": "Hi @qfrank! Thank you for investigation.\r\n\r\n> Hi @pavloburykh , can you reproduce this bug in airplane mode?\r\n\r\nNo, the bug is not reproducible in airplane mode.\r\n\r\n> I tried connect device to a network that has no access to internet with my iphone, but no luck to reproduce\r\n\r\nI have tried and noticed that indeed, initial bug with endless logout is not reproducible anymore. I have once managed to catch long logout on Android but not the endless one. \r\n\r\nAt the same time I see another issue, this time related to endless login. \r\n\r\n### Unable to login the app after logout if user was connected to the network without access to internet\r\n\r\n**Steps:** \r\n\r\n1. Connect device to a network that has no access to internet (or simulate poor connection in emulator)\r\n2. Login the app\r\n3. Perform manual logout\r\n4. Perform login right after logout\r\n5. See if user can successfully login\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** user gets stuck on on login page and is not redirected into the account. User is able to login after app re-launching. \r\n\r\n[Status-debug-logs (94).zip](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/files/13872823/Status-debug-logs.94.zip)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/97245802/80edb356-6204-4761-bbe8-6853422d01df\r\n\r\n**Expected result:** user is able to login. \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
